{"id": "EUVD-2022-55507", "enisaUuid": "efd19608-dd93-3471-aaf9-55bd75f99468", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nrapidio: fix possible UAF when kfifo_alloc() fails\n\nIf kfifo_alloc() fails in mport_cdev_open(), goto err_fifo and just free\npriv. But priv is still in the chdev->file_list, then list traversal\nmay cause UAF. This fixes the following smatch warning:\n\ndrivers/rapidio/devices/rio_mport_cdev.c:1930 mport_cdev_open() warn: '&priv->list' not removed from list", "datePublished": "2025-09-15T15:31:22", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-24T21:30:56", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2a6c75adf8192f07ddcdd4a1a13488c890a73919", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2dfd60724d271a6ab99f93f40f38f2ced1ddbb87", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a253dde0403a153075ffb254f6f7b2635e49e97a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/311b488405ac45af46756b1c8f1d27007b68b07e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5ee850645e42f541ce1ea8130c2b27cc495f965c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2f5cc7fd73fd6253cc71214f0dd499cc62feb469", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2ba06e57f933f0eac242e8b389433da1cc00d4d5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/cb87af2c19c0993f6e21f75b963a5599c5a73e76", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/02d7d89f816951e0862147d751b1150d67aaebdd", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50245"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50245"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "005aa97e-cd9d-357e-bcb2-9573803fcb8c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "e8de370188d098bb49483c287b44925957c3c9b6 <2dfd60724d271a6ab99f93f40f38f2ced1ddbb87"}, {"id": "0b992a7d-0b46-3c18-b7f7-8ce9705d5ae2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.163"}, {"id": "206e1fd4-4765-3aaa-a874-1923325b0013", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2"}, {"id": "28375dc6-ba5b-3c91-a3dd-a0034108206f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "e8de370188d098bb49483c287b4492